FESI.Interpreter
Class EcmaScriptEvaluateVisitor

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--FESI.Interpreter.EcmaScriptEvaluateVisitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
EcmaScriptConstants, EcmaScriptVisitor
public class EcmaScriptEvaluateVisitor
extends Object
implements EcmaScriptVisitor, EcmaScriptConstants

The evaluate visitor use the visitor pattern to evaluate the parsed code. Use for both main program and functions (using different entries). A new evaluator is used everytime as it contains the return code (because we can return only one variable).

The parse tree must have been preprocessed by the variable and function visitors first.

acceptNull

protected static ESValue acceptNull(Object v)
To transform a null (empty) result (but not an ESNull!) in 'ESUndefined'. null results may be returned if a statement as the empty statement, missing else clause of an if statement, loop not executed at all, etc.. is executed for value (for example as the last statement of a called function used in an assignement). This is a programming error, and it may be useful to modify this function to generate an exception during debugging. However other implementation seem to accept ESUndefined in these cases. The standard is not totally clear to me.

An alternative would be to return ESUndefined in all cases, but then we lose a useful distinction (at least for debugging...).

A couple of tests are done in visit(ASTCompositeReference node, ... too.
